Long Island Investment Adviser Sued by SEC for Fraud

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-09-28T17:37:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/long-island-investment-adviser-sued-by-sec-for-fraud.html
 Corey Ribotsky, a Long Island-
based investment adviser who runs NIR Group LLC, was sued by the
Securities and Exchange Commission for defrauding investors and
misappropriating more than $1 million.  Ribotsky specialized in PIPE transactions, or private
investment in public equity, the SEC said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  